  "elapsed_s": 4.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But for me, as a teacher in physical education was very important, because I could make extra money by teaching children or anybody else.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, I stayed with my family.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I never--",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I stayed at home.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I have a wonderful family, warm relationship with my parents and with my sister, and we were an extremely loving family.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "My parents protected and sheltered us and tried to do everything possible for the children, and--",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Is a--  is interesting question what you are asking me to answer.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "In my youth-- in my youth, I never saw any [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] anti-Semitic against me personally.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "There were some story, what you hear, that something happened, sometime maybe over exaggerate.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Because the anti-Semitism in Poland, what we consider was the biggest country with the biggest anti-Semitism, is a very over-- over exaggerate.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Poland, in general terms, was not more or less anti-Semitic than in Germany or France.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I even consider the Frenchman and Englishman and German more anti-Semitic inclined because they do this in the white gloves.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And a Polack, when he didn't like you, he told you, you dirty Jews, and this was everything over.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, this I-- I watched the history of Hitler from the beginning, from about 1928, when he becames to take little power and was lot of story written in the papers and things like this.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we knew that this man is really a danger to society, not only in the Germany, but for influence also every other country around him, like France, Czechoslovakia, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] Croatia, Yugoslavia, Hungary, Poland.",
      "word_count": 37
    }
  ],
